I found an issue that had a "duplicates" link to it, when it should have just been a "relates to" link, however the Manage Links page only gives me the option to delete the link, not edit it.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3063].
  {panel}

On Browse Project screen, under Open Issues, you currently show counts of open issues by Component and by Version. It would be GREAT if you would also show Count by Type in the same way. See attached file for a mockup of the screen with example layout.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3055].
  {panel}

Currently, one can subscribe to reports and have them sent via email in either Text or HTML format.  It is important we be able to have this sent to a server where they can be stored and viewed.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3048].
  {panel}

Now user must do 2 jumps from hi's task list - the first jump from task list (on dashboard) to task details, and the second one from details to "LogWork".
It would be much more convinient to be able to jump directly from task list to work reporting for daily reports, or do work logging right at the task list page (througth the popup window, for example).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3047].
  {panel}

Could You add to "Log work" page reporting by percents of work сompleted, instead of (or with) reporting by Time spent or Remaining Work estimate ?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3034].
  {panel}

A feature request that has come from my development team is the ability to "Request Comment/Update/More Info", which would mail the indicated person (either an email address or registered user) with the Issue ID, an appropriate link, and possibly a comment logged at time of 'requesting update/comment', so that developers could get feedback/guidance on issues on request, as opposed to reassigning the issue in question (which is the only alternative we can see), as the developer would still be working on the issue, but wants to keep all info inside the jira workflow rather than taking questions etc offline and loosing some context for the issue.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3031].
  {panel}

I mailed a JIRA instance with POPping set up, but from an address that was not the one I was registered on JIRA with. It seems the message was silently ignored - it would be great if a reply could be sent that gave an error message.
